1.1. Histograms

The histogram of the home goals is plotted.

ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTHG), binwidth=0.5,fill="purple")+
  xlab("Home Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Home Goals")

The histogram of the away goals is plotted.

ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTAG), binwidth=0.5,fill="darkblue")+
  xlab("Away Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Away Goals")

The histogram of the difference between home goals and away goals is plotted.

ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTHG-FTAG), binwidth=0.5,fill="orange")+
  xlab("Home Goals-Away Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Home Goals-Away Goals")

1.2. Histograms with Distributions

The histogram of home goals looks like it is distributed with Poisson.

hist_home<-ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTHG), binwidth=0.5,fill="purple")+
  xlab("Home Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Home Goals with Poisson Distribution")
xfit = seq(0,max(data[,"FTHG"]),1)
yfit = dpois(xfit,lambda=mean(data[,"FTHG"]))
yfit<-yfit*length(data[,"FTHG"])
home_fits<-data.frame(xfit,yfit)
hist_home+
  geom_line(data=home_fits,aes(x=xfit,y=yfit),color="brown",size=1.5)

The histogram of away goals looks like it is distributed with Poisson.

hist_away<-ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTAG), binwidth=0.5,fill="darkblue")+
  xlab("Away Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Away Goals with Poisson Distribution")
xfit = seq(0,max(data[,"FTAG"]),1)
yfit = dpois(xfit,lambda=mean(data[,"FTAG"]))
yfit<-yfit*length(data[,"FTAG"])
away_fits<-data.frame(xfit,yfit)
hist_away+
  geom_line(data=away_fits,aes(x=xfit,y=yfit),color="orange",size=1.5)

The histogram of the difference between home and away goals looks like it is distributed with Skellam (difference of two Poissons).

diff_hist<-ggplot(data) + geom_histogram(aes(x = FTHG-FTAG), binwidth=0.5,fill="orange")+
  xlab("Home Goals-Away Goals") + ylab("Number of Games") + ggtitle("Histogram of Home Goals-Away Goals with Skellam Distribution")
xfit = seq(-10,10,1)
yfit = dskellam(xfit,lambda1=mean(data$FTHG),lambda2=mean(data$FTAG))
yfit=yfit*length(data$FTHG)
diff_fits<-data.frame(xfit,yfit)
diff_hist+geom_line(data=diff_fits,aes(x=xfit,y=yfit),color="darkgreen",size=1.5)

2.Task2

For the bookmaker Bet365, the probability calculations are done and they are normalized.

Bet365

data<-data%>% mutate(prob_home_365=1/B365H)
data<-data%>% mutate(prob_away_365=1/B365A)
data<-data%>% mutate(prob_draw_365=1/B365D)
data<-data%>% mutate(total_prob_365=(prob_home_365+prob_draw_365+prob_away_365))
data<-data%>% mutate(normalized_home_365=prob_home_365/total_prob_365)
data<-data%>% mutate(normalized_away_365=prob_away_365/total_prob_365)
data<-data%>% mutate(normalized_draw_365=prob_draw_365/total_prob_365)
head(data[,69:75])

The bins are created for Bet365 with the intervals of 0.05. By counting the number of “draw” match results and dividing them by the total number of games in the corresponding bin, the estimated probabilities are obtained.

bins=seq(-1,1,0.05)
draw<-data%>%filter(FTR=="D")

draw<-draw%>%mutate(interval_365=cut(draw$normalized_home_365-draw$normalized_away_365,bins))
data<-data%>%mutate(interval_365=cut(data$normalized_home_365-data$normalized_away_365,bins))
counted<-draw%>%group_by(interval_365)%>%count()
counted_all<-data%>%group_by(interval_365)%>%count()
ratio<-merge(counted,counted_all,by="interval_365")
ratio<-ratio%>%mutate(ratio=n.x/n.y)
x<-data%>%group_by(interval_365)%>%summarise(meandiff=mean(normalized_home_365-normalized_away_365))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
ratio<-merge(ratio,x,by="interval_365")

As get close to the mean, actual results have higher values than the company’s probability. So, one can potentially make money in the long run by betting on “Draw” for the games whose odds reside in the corresponding bin.

ggplot(data=data,aes(x=normalized_home_365-normalized_away_365, y=normalized_draw_365))+
  geom_point(color="yellow")+geom_point(data=ratio,aes(meandiff,ratio),color="green",size=2,shape=15)+
  theme_dark()+xlab("P(Home) – P(Away)") + ylab("P(Tie)") + ggtitle("Bet365")
